Rare Power / 3 :e_snecko: / The Snecko

~~- **Snekproof.** -~~
Whenever you play an **Offclass** card, draw 1 card.

messages.content: Love that it upgrades to remove snekproof, that's such a fun concept
I think it would've been fine to keep it at 3 cost tbh
admittedly, how else would you upgrade it instead
2 cost is cursed
+1 card drawn is straight up busted

An extremely powerful form, it does cost quite a lot to get it in play (though upgrading it can do wonders to help with this, if you have a reasonable amount of muddle), but once you have it down, it usually draws at least 3 cards a turn. It can do far more than that it you have additional energy gain, or lots of muddle/master eye/snecko eye to set cards to 0 cost, and can be a huge win condition to just slam 10+ cards a turn and win through sheer numbers (not having to deal with time eater and beat of death makes this much more viable than it would be in traditional mode)
also you can use this to do the unceasing top anger infinite
without unceasing top

A card I am hoping to see basically every time I play snecko, will pay gold for in a store, it's a great scaling solution. It just asks so little of you, all your unidentified cards are offclass already, as well as some of your starter cards, and muddle is already great on snecko for several other synergies (playing high cost cards, spamming cards set to 0, helping smooth out master eye/snecko eye). I think this might be the best form card in downfall (the upgraded version of slime bosses form is right up there too)
Duplicated Form+ is basically just bad Deva Form + bad Echo Form
but that's still worth quite a bit more than just a deva form or just an echo form
that being said, what about Eternal Form
even nerfed on average it's +4 energy per turn

I think of hermit as a traditional mode character, and yes, eternal form is fantastic, basically a deva form that requires 0 turns to scale up, pair it with any card draw and it's a huge win condition
I've personally seen Exotic Form as "how to make an infinite out of things that should've never been part of infinites: the card"
and yes, I do think it's busted

One of the strongest things about exotic form+ is that in comparison to other scaling cards and forms, it can regularly cost as little as 0 or 1 with some synergy cards. And unlike demon form, deva form, echo form, and eternal form, it can give you immediate impact the turn you play it. You can start drawing cards with this right away and recover the cost of the card. You just don't lose tempo with exotic form+ in the same way you do with a lot of other scaling cards in slay the spire.
Very op card generally
The change to muddle makes maintaining an infinite slightly harder but not nearly enough to matter
And <Abbacus> provides block for fun eater and hearts beat of death
